# nanogent top-level gitignore. Everything else in .nanogent/
# (nanogent.mjs, config.json, prompt.md, tools/, Dockerfile,
# docker-compose.yml) is safe to commit so the team can share it.

# Safety default: any file named .env under .nanogent/ is a secret file,
# regardless of whether it belongs to core or to a tool. Never commit one.
.env

# Core runtime state only — history, jobs, learnings.
# The leading slash anchors this to .nanogent/, so tool state directories
# (.nanogent/tools/<name>/state/) are NOT matched by this rule. Each tool
# manages its own state and ships its own .gitignore if it wants anything
# in its folder ignored.
/state/
